review_blob: This is one of the best surprises! A great combination of bitterness with fruity scents. It is one of the best IPAs I had in Dublin. A Good fight for Full sail / Punk IPA

Interesting try in the "Black sheep" in Dublin. Not as extaordinary as "Of foam and fury" but carries an interesting mixture of hoppinnes and sweetness. The best part about it is the after taste - very balanced so u can carry on for long with this one.
Great tasting IPA. Unlike other IPAs it lacks the fruity scent to start with. The taste is good with a good sense of bitterness to make it balanced through the pint
It is a nice Ipa but lacks the edginess of other irish IPA. It has a strong aftertaste of a german weiss beer...not a big fan of that
Its a good one that knocks you out while being refreshing and suitable for both hot and cold weather.
beer_name: Galway Bay Of Foam and Fury

review_blob:
Amazing combination of green tea coffee and Pale ale.
Smioth with so many interesting after tastes. Must try this one if you encounter it. Scents of passionfruit and mango comes out of this one.

One of the most complete IPAs I had. From the first sniff until the last drop in the glass. A perfect IPA pint. Scent is very fruity yet the bitterness makes the taste strong for the entire pint not leaving a sour aftertaste
Great beer for hot daysm I am not a big fan of blonde beers but this one despite the misleading look had a great taste and did the job on a hot parisian day
